  "title": "Understanding Generators",
  "lessonText": "Generators are a powerful feature in Python for creating iterators in a memory-efficient way.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- Generators use the `yield` statement.\n- They produce values one at a time, on demand.\n- They help save memory compared to lists.\n- Useful for handling large datasets.\n- Can be created using generator functions or generator expressions."
  }
}
